    "updated_at": "2012-01-31T16:15:06Z",
    "body": "I don't see this as a problem. We are certainly not going to prohibit semicolons in blocks. They are very useful. I could see a warning if some branches of an if or alt have no tail expression while others do, though I am inclined against it as any real problem will be caught by type checker. I am going to close this issue but feel free to add to #1195 concerning a warning if you feel that would be appropriate.\n\n_Sent via Hubroid_\n",
